    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-27T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-27T14:00:00-05:00" n="710"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2724: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-27T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 27, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. Reference Legation’s No. 161 of October 20, forwarding draft of proposed
                    note modifying law on the budget and public accounting of July 4, 1933.</p>
                <p>Minister of Foreign Affairs accepts our draft. Please cable authorization to
                    effect exchange of notes.<note n="91" xml:id="d710fn91">Telegram No. 114,
                        October 30, 1933, 5 p.m., to the Minister in Haiti, granted the
                        authorization.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
